ent-CrateAmmunitionSmall = old wooden crate
    .desc = A small wooden crate with faded paint and the emblem of the USSP.
ent-CrateAmmunitionSmallLightRifle = old wooden crate
    .suffix = Filled
    .desc = A small wooden crate with faded paint and the emblem of the USSP. On the inside of the lid, a barely readable instruction about .30 calibre ammunition.
ent-CrateAmmunitionSmallLightRifleAP = old wooden crate
    .suffix = Filled, AP
    .desc = A small wooden crate with faded paint and the emblem of the USSP. On the inside of the lid, a barely readable instruction about 7.62x54R AP ammunition.
ent-CrateAmmunitionSmallLightRifleIncendiary = old wooden crate
    .suffix = Filled, Incendiary
    .desc = A small wooden crate with faded paint and the emblem of the USSP. On the inside of the lid, a barely readable instruction about 7.62x54R incendiary ammunition.
ent-CrateShelfMosin = old wooden crate
    .suffix = Filled
    .desc = A large wooden crate with faded paint and the emblem of the USSP. On the inside of the lid, a barely readable instruction explains the importance of the bayonet and which part of the rifle to hold to kill properly. Judging by the dust, it’s been waiting for centuries. Warning: Instructions may be outdated by several centuries.
ent-WrappedMosin = wrapped mosin rifle
    .desc = An ancient Kardashev-Mosin rifle, hermetically sealed in packing paper and drenched in cosmic grease. Forgotten, waiting for a war that never came. Ammunition not included, but at least you’ve got a bayonet!
ent-CrateAmmunitionSmallDragunov = old wooden crate
    .suffix = Filled, Sniper
    .desc = A small wooden crate with faded paint and the emblem of the USSP. Inside is an old marksman rifle and spare magazines.
ent-CrateAmmunitionSmallDP28 = old wooden crate
    .suffix = Filled, DP-28
    .desc = A small wooden crate with faded paint and the emblem of the USSP. Inside is a DP-28 light machine gun.
ent-CrateAmmunitionSmallSKM24 = old wooden crate
    .suffix = Filled, SKM-24
    .desc = A small wooden crate with faded paint and the emblem of the USSP. Inside is an SKM-24 rifle with spare magazines.
